TCP Simple Gateway

Copyright (C) 2002 Juan Fajardo

TCPSG is just a simple tcp port forwarder designed to distribute a service 
using a virtual server. 

main features:

- TCP Port Simple redirect
- Simple load balancing 
- Priority based service distribution 
- Availability based service distribution

Homepage:   http://tcpsg.sourceforge.net/

The main code is pretty simple, and part of it is based on portfw developed by
Bruno A. Costa (bcostaf@codata.com.br)

NOTE> It's just a pre-alpha, so maybe there are many bugs, please don't forget
send me any comments or suggestions

thanks for using tcpsg.

jfajardo@unillanos.edu.co


